<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Video Displays</title>

  <style>
    .font-size-controls {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      z-index: 10;
      background: transparent;
      padding: 8px 0 12px;
      text-align: right;
    }

    .font-size-controls button {
      background: none;
      border: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin-left: 10px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .font-size-controls i {
      font-size: 50px;
      /* make icon larger */
      color: white;
      /* force white icon */
      opacity: 0.5;
    }


    .showcase-talking-points {
      --talking-point-size: 18px;
      font-size: var(--talking-point-size);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points.size-small {
      --talking-point-size: 16px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points.size-medium {
      --talking-point-size: 18px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points.size-large {
      --talking-point-size: 22px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points {
      background: #1F1646;
      padding: 16px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      width: 100%;
      max-height: 100%;
      overflow-y: auto;
      overflow-x: hidden;
      -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points h1 {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points h2 {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      margin-top: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points ul {
      margin-left: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details {
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points summary {
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
      transform-origin: left center;
      --step: 0.1s;
      animation: productPulse 1s ease-in-out 1;
      animation-delay: 0.8s;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(1) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 0);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(2) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 1);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(3) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 2);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(4) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 3);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(5) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 4);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(6) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 5);
    }

    .showcase-talking-points details:nth-of-type(7) summary {
      animation-delay: calc(0.8s + var(--step) * 6);
    }

    @keyframes productPulse {

      0%,
      100% {
        transform: translateX(0);
        opacity: 1;
      }

      15% {
        transform: translateX(6px);
        opacity: 0.85;
      }

      30% {
        transform: translateX(0);
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }

    .showcase-talking-points hr {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid #ccc;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .showcase-talking-points .instruction {
      text-align: center;
      animation: instructionBlink 1.6s ease-in-out 1 forwards;
      animation-delay: 3s;
    }

    @keyframes instructionBlink {
      0% {
        opacity: 1;
      }

      15% {
        opacity: 0;
      }

      30% {
        opacity: 1;
      }

      45% {
        opacity: 0;
      }

      60% {
        opacity: 1;
      }

      100% {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }

    .showcase-talking-points summary {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 24px;
      /* space for arrow */
    }

    /* arrow */
    .showcase-talking-points summary::after {
      content: "▸";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 50%;
      transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(0deg);
      transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    }

    /* rotate when open */
    .showcase-talking-points details[open] summary::after {
      transform: translateY(-50%) rotate(90deg);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <script>
    const sizes = ['size-small', 'size-medium', 'size-large'];
    let current = 1; // start at medium

    function changeFontSize(direction) {
      const page = document.querySelector('.showcase-talking-points');

      current += direction;

      // clamp so it doesn't go out of bounds
      if (current < 0) current = 0;
      if (current > sizes.length - 1) current = sizes.length - 1;

      page.classList.remove(...sizes);
      page.classList.add(sizes[current]);
    }

    // set default on load
    window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      document.querySelector('.showcase-talking-points')
        .classList.add(sizes[current]);
    });
  </script>

  <div class="showcase-talking-points">

    <div class="font-size-controls">
      <button onclick="changeFontSize(-1)">
        <i class="icons8-minus"></i>
      </button>
      <button onclick="changeFontSize(1)">
        <i class="icons8-plus"></i>
      </button>
    </div>

    <h1>Video Displays</h1>

    <ul>
      <li>Human learning derived from visual information increases understanding and retention while solidifying long-lasting mental connections. From traditional projectors and monitors to vibrant LED and emerging e-ink, Encore's video display solutions provide the tools to deliver event messaging effectively.</li>
      <li>Encore offers a comprehensive portfolio of video technologies including large-format projection and monitors, direct view LED, and boardroom-style displays. Whether for signage, presentations, or presenter support, Encore has the right display solution for any customer need.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr>
    <p class="instruction">↓ Tap a product name below to view individual talking points ↓</p>
    <details>
      <summary>LED Banners</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore’s LED Banner product is a tower style, direct view LED display that can serve as vibrant digital signage or a dynamic scenic set piece. Whether used standalone to provide integral event messaging or linked together to create a large digital canvas, LED Banners are ideal in high ambient light conditions where traditional video display technologies may lack clarity and definition.</li>
        <li>LED displays have traditionally been large, modular, semi-permanent installations. LED Banners brings this professional technology in a more user-friendly package.</li>
        <li>LED Banners can be used in many configurations. Standalone refers to utilizing a single LED Banner as the complete display. Linked refers to using anywhere between 2 – 6 LED Banners in an interconnected way to display a single image across multiple units. This makes the LED Banner product extremely versatile.</li>
        <li>LED Banners can display the right content at the right time. With the scheduling feature, LED Banners will change the displayed event messaging based on desired timings.</li>
        <li>Equipped with an onboard media player and external HDMI input, LED Banners can scale with a customer’s content playback needs.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Touch Monitor Kiosk</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore is currently researching touch monitor Kiosks</li>
        <li>Portrait 55” monitor housed in a sleek all in one aluminum cabinet</li>
        <li>4K resolution and 500 nits of peak brightness</li>
        <li>Sleek and slim design</li>
        <li>10-point Infrared (IR) touch with &lt;10ms response time</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Newline Interactive Display</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>The Newline Z Series is a 4K touchscreen display that allows for content mirroring, touch control, video conferencing, whiteboarding, and annotation with exhaustive connectivity options for customer and Encore computers, as well as an onboard PC with full Windows functionality.</li>
        <li>At its core, the Newline Z Series can perform as a meeting’s focal point with a 4K UHD resolution panel and 400 nits maximum brightness.</li>
        <li>Using Projected Capacitive Touch (PCAP) technology, the Z Series can accurately accept up to 20 simultaneous touchpoints. This allows for uninhibited collaboration, even with two users at the display.</li>
        <li>With the included stylus, users can naturally write and annotate atop their meeting content to highlight specific messaging or engage attendees with a live whiteboarding session.</li>
        <li>The Newline Z Series is equipped with full Windows functionality via a slot-style computer, offering users the interface with which they are most comfortable.</li>
        <li>With an HDMI video output, the Z Series can be displayed on large keynote displays to bring the audience into a live ideation session.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Ultra Stretch Monitor</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore’s Ultra Stretch monitor solution steps outside of standard aspect ratio constraints to deliver event messaging in a unique and memorable way. At 86 inches wide, the Ultra Stretch signage display cannot be ignored.</li>
        <li>Capable of operation in portrait, landscape, or four picture-by-picture configurations, Ultra Stretch is flexible in creating the best customer experience.</li>
        <li>Sporting a 58:9 aspect ratio and UHD resolution of 3840 x 600, the Ultra Stretch is designed to command attendee attention and ensure message reception.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Portable LED Display</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore’s Portable LED display is an all-in-one video display that boasts quick setup, convenient portability, and dynamic LED display technology in a pre-assembled design. Encore Portable LED display features a foldable screen design and motorized height adjustment that allows for streamlined operation and near immediate deployment.</li>
        <li>Direct view LED video displays offer incredible benefits but often have a high technical barrier of entry. Encore’s Portable LED distills this complex technology into plug-and-play operation near identical to a television.</li>
        <li>Direct view LED display technology shines in challenging lighting situations where projection and traditional displays may be too dim.</li>
        <li>Encore’s Portable LED display covers many small meeting needs with one device. With integrated speakers, comprehensive connectivity, and wireless sharing capabilities Encore’s Portable LED display delivers the ingredients for successful message delivery.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>E-Ink Display</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore has done some research into E-Ink display technology and though the technology is exciting and new, we must take pause at its current point while we continue to let it grow and evolve. With points like high costs, limited display sizes, and limited use cases, we will continue to keep an eye on this technology as it evolves.</li>
        <li>Eco-friendly display solution that uses close to zero energy</li>
        <li>With no backlighting, these styled displays must be in well lit areas</li>
        <li>Built-in signage system (not a typical monitor)</li>
        <li>Higher in price than a typical monitor with fewer use cases</li>
        <li>Not available for rent with no sub-rental opportunities</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>LED Panels (LED Wall)</summary>
      <ul>
        <li>Encore owns and operates thousands of direct view LED panels from industry leading manufacturers. “LED Wall” products like these are celebrated for their high brightness, modularity, and excellent image quality. This setup exemplifies the modularity and creativity that can be applied to LED deployments with Encore.</li>
        <li>Highest brightness / visibility video display technology currently available for live events. Great when ambient lighting can’t be controlled.</li>
        <li>Modular design allows for near infinite combinations of setups from more standard 16:9 displays to large custom aspect ratio canvases.</li>
        <li>Features superior contrast and black levels when compared to projection leading to better overall image quality.</li>
      </ul>
    </details>

  </div>

</body>

</html>
